<subSubSection id="6A17D063899804AD3717FF64040BDB1C" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" type="type">
<paragraph id="D674F4265A53581BB6076178BCA86B9F" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B85E0ED1869E562AD3D0737DF09FF6B2" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
TURKEY, Merzivan, 
<emphasis id="C58ACFA0346975F7A72BB09470553A05" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Manisadjan</emphasis>
s.n. (holotype W!).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="55C242AD81C82CBE2791ECC077F9B40E" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" type="description">
<paragraph id="4F9822004361A2846A3E7F52A6191911" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="323581EECBED17DBF809F90320F2F162" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
Presumably trailing herb of unknown length; stems and leaves pubescent. Leaves similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="B7BA9584349D7E74BFB3F69CAC5C2ED5" authorityName="Mill., Gard. Dict. ed. 8: no. 20. 1768. (Miller" authorityYear="1768" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus betonicifolius" order="Solanales" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="betonicifolius">
<emphasis id="9DB2C25628A62A5302951DE510568E1F" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Convolvulus betonicifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, petiolate, c. 2.5 
<normalizedToken id="8BD26A5F07C3C146FF7F5431464B8BC3" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2 cm, ovate, obtuse and mucronate, entire, shallowly sagittate with short auricles. Flowers 1-2, pedunculate, axillary; peduncles c. 2.5 cm; bracteoles c. 5 
<normalizedToken id="B1631F4FE8199CEE412A3E77E75FD1C4" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5 mm, linear, attenuate; pedicels equalling bracts; sepals 6 
<normalizedToken id="FE08B6E89299D6A4AADDAEB678CC5B88" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3 mm, oblong-oblanceolate, obtuse and retuse, mucronulate, pubescent, inner sepals glabrous, membranous; corolla 2.5 cm long, colour unknown, midpetaline bands pubescent, unlobed; filaments glandular below; ovary glabrous, style 8 mm long, glabrous, stigmas 5 mm. Capsule and seeds unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BD5354C572A766EAA4BF24B8840C93A3" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="CD44B896C452CC6BB644DCA0552A2971" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F08EE1D210EABA93961727CCF64A380D" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Turkey. Only known from the type collection.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="39B354F3B2B8126177653BCB96C0242E" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" type="notes">
<paragraph id="B2F8DC267382A308A0087FF2256E2168" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E0098DC7DD54DCE6D8FD6997A831DE8A" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
This species is not conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="CCA9DC254AA0C144B34197CD5DF23D05" authorityName="L., Sp. Pl. 1: 153. 1753. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus arvensis" order="Solanales" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arvensis">
<emphasis id="26622DEAC58DE000F5A8708E2E848D62" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Convolvulus arvensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as stated in the 
<emphasis id="8E766AADE093A34303FC9C9EB221A221" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Flora of Turkey</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="F37D8133AA3B3E04B6E70EEE143B5DB1" author="Parris, BS" journalOrPublisher="Flora of Turkey" pageId="208" pageNumber="209" pagination="198 - 219" refId="B256" refString="Parris, BS, 1978. Convolvulus. Flora of Turkey volume 6: 198 - 219" title="Convolvulus." volume="volume 6" year="1978">Parris 1978</bibRefCitation>
) but differs in the pubescent leaves and the pubescent, 6 mm long, herbaceous sepals which lack a membranous border. Instead it is clearly related to the very variable 
<taxonomicName id="A28DA25A4E758A5E6C0B4422C8BD196A" authorityName="Mill., Gard. Dict. ed. 8: no. 20. 1768. (Miller" authorityYear="1768" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus betonicifolius" order="Solanales" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="betonicifolius">
<emphasis id="907A64FAC24C4B27E113101B36411CEA" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Convolvulus betonicifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as stated by 
<normalizedToken id="450F0882F7B88380543B68EBAC3B479B" originalValue="Sa’ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
, but appears to be distinct as we cannot match it with any specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="981BC7EB8FB45E19E542A1EAAB9B2049" authorityName="Mill., Gard. Dict. ed. 8: no. 20. 1768. (Miller" authorityYear="1768" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus betonicifolius" order="Solanales" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="betonicifolius">
<emphasis id="72833F9EDAA0F47983B0FC04152C799B" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Convolvulus betonicifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It differs in the shorter, obtuse and minutely retuse sepals 5-6 mm long, which lack a distinctive apical portion. The ovary is also glabrous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
